verbose_text: In DRG neurons treated with TNF-alpha (40 ng/ml) in the presence of WIN-55 (400 ng/ml), selective CB2 antagonist JTE907 but not selective CB1 antagonist MJ15 largely blocked the inhibitory effect of WIN-55 on TNF-alpha-induced expression of nNOS (XREF_FIG) and NOS activity (XREF_FIG).
evidence: CB2 antagonist JTE907 but not selective CB1 antagonist MJ15 largely blocked the inhibitory effect of WIN-55
